OL,3,CThird of youth crimes committed by
OL,4,Csame ten children in Jersey
OL,6,FJersey's Chief of Police says
OL,7,Fcriminalising children is not the
OL,8,Fanswer when it comes to tackling youth
OL,9,Fcrime, despite a rise in offences.
OL,11,FIt comes as the Government revealed
OL,12,Fthe Youth Justice Roadmap, which lays
OL,13,Fout a new prevention plan and an
OL,14,Fapproach for when children commit a
OL,15,Fcrime, focusing on their rights and
OL,16,Ffuture rather than just punishment.
