OL,3,CThird of youth crimes committed by
OL,4,Csame ten children in Jersey
OL,6,FOn whether he agrees with the focus on
OL,7,Fkeeping children out of prison where
OL,8,Fpossible, Robin Smith explains:
OL,9,F"Wholeheartedly ... what police
OL,10,Fofficers want more than anything is
OL,11,Fnot to be arresting young people and
OL,12,Fnot putting them before the courts.
OL,14,F"We had about 800 crimes committed by
OL,15,Fpeople under the age of 18 in 2024, a
OL,16,F13% increase (on 2023).
OL,18,F"About 280 of those crimes are by a
OL,19,Fvery small group, around 10 young
OL,20,Fpeople committing repeated crimes.
OL,26,@xD@NpmxD@Vpn
